post_text: Giddings ISD would like to thank Hal Bowman for the motivational words he recently shared with our faculty and staff. We would like to share his message and words of encouragement with the entire GISD community in the hope that you might also find nuggets of wisdom in his message that will encourage you during this challenging time in our lives. Hal reminds us “The greater the challenge, the greater the lesson.” Thank you Hal for your message, and thank you to the families of GISD for your support in helping us in our mission to educate your children. Watch here: https://bit.ly/BowmanMessage

post_text:
Good afternoon. Giddings Independent School District has announced that all facilities will be closed to everyone other than essential staff until further notice.

All GISD campuses will be providing home based lessons for students.

Teachers are busy preparing those lessons this week.

Details on how to access those lessons will be provided at a later time.

Meal service for students will begin on Monday, March 23. Drive-thru pick-up will be available at the Giddings Elementary School at the north side bus lane from 9am through noon Monday through Friday. Per Texas Department of Agriculture guidelines, children receiving meals must be present in the vehicle. More details of meal service are available on the GISD website.

post_text:
All GISD schools will be closed for the remainder of the week.

UIL has also postponed all competitions. Additionally, practices, rehearsals, and workouts that occur outside the school day also postponed.

Classes will resume at their normal time beginning on Monday, March 23. Buses will run on their regular schedules.

If you or a member of your immediate family has traveled outside of the area in the last 14 says, please check the GISD website for return-to-school guidelines. As always, if you have fever, cough, or have trouble breathing, stay at home and seek medical attention.

post_text: The rumor of a threat of violence surfaced at GHS. Every aspect of investigation by GISD and ultimately the investigation by Giddings PD failed to yield any credible evidence of the threat. All information was determined to be rumor. Current rumors on social media have taken many forms, but are still nothing more than rumors. An informational post from Giddings Police Department is shown here.
shared_text:
Giddings Police Department
October 2, 2019 at 7:50 PM ·

There has been a lot of misinformation and rumors put out by parents and students over the past two days about a threat at the Giddings School. It is NOT true. In fact it has been looked into by the school and found to be false. There is no active investigation. If you have questions you can contact the police department or the GISD.

Giddings Middle School
August 14, 2019 at 5:15 PM ·

GMS Principal Charlotte Penn provided this update after the first day of school:
It was a great First Day at Giddings Middle School. I would like to remind parents of a couple of things. When dropping off students in the morning, please do not stop in the passing lane to drop off students. This is very dangerous. Please be mindful of student safety. Also, breakfast for students begins at 7:25 a.m. and ends at 7:40 a.m. From the cafeteria, breakfast students will go to the gym where they will be released to class at 7:45 a.m. Giddings Middle School Classes begin promptly at 7:50 a.m. School dismisses at 3:25 p.m. All transportation changes should be made via the Giddings Middle School prior to 2:15 p.m. The office number is 979-542-2057. Thank you for your support. The entire Giddings Middle School Staff and Administration appreciates your support and looks forward to another great year.

post_text: Drop-off & pick-up instructions for Giddings Intermediate School
shared_text:
Giddings Intermediate School
August 13, 2019 at 8:52 PM ·

We will have 2 lanes open for car drop off and pick up.
Each lane will need to pull to the very end, and the next 3 cars will line up in the order of the cones. 1-4
Students will exit vehicle, walk on sidewalk then walk across crosswalk into the school. After the students have exited the vehicle, the lines will be dismissed one at a time.
We will repeat this process until all of our students have entered.

**Reminder- 4 cars pull all the way up, stop, unload, then exit when you are directed.

We are hoping this makes your drop off/pick up at school smoother! Thank you all for helping us with this adjustment.

post_text:
2019-2020 School Vaccine Requirements

According to the Texas Minimum State Vaccine Requirements for Students Grades K-12, students who are entering school are required to have their immunizations up to date. Students entering 7th Grade are required to have an immunization update (booster).

Please see the following, for information about these boosters and all other school vaccine requirements:
https://www.dshs.texas.gov/immunize/school/school-requirements.aspx

According to the State of Texas, no student will be allowed to attend school without their immunizations being up to date. Students will not receive their class schedules for the 2019-2020 school year until all immunization requirements are met.

It is not too early to get your child vaccinated for the next school year. Please do not wait until time for school to start as the vaccine supply may be low. Please bring a copy of your child’s shot record to school, when they receive their vaccinations, so the school records can be updated.

post_text:
We have already received a tremendous outpouring of support from our community and those around us because of the fire in our baseball field house on the morning of March 20, 2019.

We appreciate everything our community and others are willing to do to help our student-athletes. We will be issuing a statement soon on how to handle any donations that groups or individuals would like to make. It is important to follow a process that does not violate UIL rules or jeopardize the students' amateur status or lead to forfeiture of games.

During her 30 years as a teacher in Giddings I.S.D., Mrs. Simmonds made a tremendous impact on generations of Giddings I.S.D. students. She will be missed by not only the staff and students of Giddings I.S.D. but by the entire community.

A service to celebrate her life will be held at 1:00 pm on Saturday, January 5, 2019 at Giddings High School.

The Buffaloes will face Houston Washington in the first round of the playoffs on Thursday, November 15th, at 7:00 PM at Buffalo Stadium in Giddings, Texas. Please come out and support the Buffaloes.

Season ticket holders may purchase their reserved tickets at the high school until noon on Wednesday, November 14th. After Wednesday at noon, all reserved tickets will be available for purchase by the public.

General Admission tickets will be $6 and Reserved Seats will be $8.

post_text:
The Giddings I.S.D. Board of Trustees unanimously voted to hire Wade Griffin as the District’s Athletic Director and Head Football Coach at their meeting on March 5, 2018. Coach Griffin previously held the same position at Fort Worth Brewer High School. He has nineteen years of overall experience including experience at both the high school and college level. Coach Griffin has had coaching stops during his career at Elgin High School, Georgetown High School, Navarro Junior College, Round Rock Westwood High School, Brookshire Royal High School, Tenaha High School, and the University of Central Oklahoma.

Coach Griffin and his wife Terra, who is also a coach, have four children, three girls and one boy. They are excited about the opportunity to move back to Central Texas and become part of the Community of Giddings. #BuffaloPride #GISDmakeanimpact

Giddings ISD coordinated an effort to donate school supplies to displaced students in Giddings ISD and La Grange ISD after Hurricane Harvey.

Tim Walther (Citizens' National Bank, Giddings Noon Lion's Club), Roger Dees (GISD Superintendent, Giddings Noon Lion's Club, Giddings Rotary Club), and Pat Jackson (Giddings ISD School Board Vice-President, Giddings New Horizons Lion's Club) drove to La Grange on Tuesday, September 5th to deliver the school supplies.

Thank you to all of the service organizations and local residents who participated in the school supply drive.

post_text:
Red Cross Donations Accepted in Giddings ISD-The American Red Cross is working around the clock along the Gulf Coast to help the thousands of people whose lives have been devastated by Hurricane Harvey including those who are displaced from their homes within the boundaries of Giddings ISD.

As a result of tremendous support the Red Cross has received, they have shifted their requests to monetary donations which will allow them to get donated supplies to those that need it most.

In order to support this cause, the Giddings High School Student Council will be accepting monetary donations at the gates of the stadium during the football game vs. Navarro. Donations will also be accepted at the Giddings High School office during the day on Friday, September 1, 2017. A presentation will be made to volunteers at the local Red Cross shelter at halftime of the game. #GISDmakeanimpact

On February 22nd, the GISD Superintendent's Advisory Council, a group of student leaders from each campus in the district, visited the State Capitol to learn more about the government and legislative process.

The group sat in the gallery of the meeting of the House of Representatives to witness the legislative process. During the session, Rep. John Cyrier recognized the group and House Resolution 207 was approved which honors the students and district.

post_text:
The Giddings ISD is hosting Social Media Day on Thursday, February 23rd.

The purpose of the event is to educate students, staff, parents, and the community on internet safety and security. Our guest speaker, Mark Seguin, will present student assemblies on each campus throughout the day and will speak at a meeting for parents and community members at 6:30 PM at the Giddings High School Cafeteria. The community event is free and childcare will be provided for your school aged children. Please RSVP to Giddings High School, at (979) 542-3351, if you will need childcare.

The student assemblies will focus on age appropriate information about cyberbullying, internet safety, and potential consequences for inappropriate use of the internet. The community meeting will focus on steps adults should take to remain safe on the internet as well as how they can help keep their children safe.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aU1ivDPVmmE

post_text:
Weather conditions occur during the winter months that could result in a school closure or delayed start. If inclement weather occurs, the District will make the official decision concerning closing or delaying the start of school based on road conditions. School will either be delayed or canceled if students and staff cannot safely travel on the roadways.

When it becomes necessary to open late, to release students early, or to cancel school, district officials will attempt to notify parents and staff by posting a message on the district website, this Facebook page, and the following radio and television stations:

Television:
KVUE-Austin
KEYE-Austin
KXAN-Austin
Radio:
KBUK-La Grange
KTEX-Brenham
KLBJ-Austin

We will also make an automated call through our online emergency notification system, School Messenger. In order to ensure that you receive all automated messages, please update your contact information with the campus attendance office.

The GHS Varsity Football Team will be playing in the second round of the playoffs in Huntsville on Friday, November 18, 2016 at 7:30 PM. The band, cheerleaders, and buffalo gals will also be traveling to the game. In order to provide enough buses and drivers to safely transport these students to Huntsville by game time, we will need to release school 2 hours early.

All campuses will dismiss their students 2 hours early on Friday, November 18, 2016. Buses will also run two hours early. As always, the safety of our students is our number one priority.

The Giddings Buffalo Varsity Football Team will face Wimberley in the home opener on Friday, September 2, 2016 at 7:30 PM. Buffalo Stadium now has additional parking for visitors on the visitor's side of the stadium.

The new visitor's parking lot can be entered from Highway 77 on the south side of the stadium. The lot was purchased from TXDOT, and the entrance is located beside the old TXDOT office building. There are an additional 250 marked parking spaces in the lot along with space for even more overflow parking.
